fields.name: Talking Tiger Lily
fields.description: Beautiful talking tiger lily. This chatty flower is the perfect addition to any garden. They will get on well with other plants and will keep you company while tending to your garden. Tiger lily care involves little work after plants are established, as they are somewhat drought tolerant. When growing tiger lilies, youâ€™ll find they often thrive with existing rainfall.

fields.name: Singing White Rose
fields.description: This rare and unique rose is the ultimate plant for any collector. This rose will have a presents in your garden that can not be ignored. Her beautiful voice will capture the ear of any visitor and will be the talking point of any party

fields.name: Painted Rose Bush
fields.description: When a standard rose bush just won't do, you need a Painted Rose Bush. Hand painted by the Queen of Hearts soldiers, this is the perfect gift for any budding gardener

fields.name: Unbirthday Party
fields.description: You are invited to the biggest party of the year. Join me Alice, Hatter and March Hare for your Unbirthday party. Complete with tea, cake and a little bit of MADNESS!

fields.name: Horn Duck
fields.description: Each Horn Duck has a yellow horn for their head as well as a purple bulb for their body

fields.name: Accordion Owl
fields.description: This red owl that can stretch its neck like an accordion. Whenever it stretches its neck, not only does it hoot but it also makes accordion sounds.

fields.name: Bread and Butterfly
fields.description: This unique creature has slices of bread for wings with butter spread on the outside of their wings

fields.name: Cage Bird
fields.description: This large bird like creature has a yellow bird cage for a body and has no wings.

fields.name: Caterpillar
fields.description: Caterpillar has a passion for grammer frequently over-emphasising certain words.

fields.name: Cheshire Cat
fields.description: Cheshire Cat has a permanent smile on his face and he can disappear at will. He is a very odd being who is able to reshape his body to either amuse or frighten his visitors.

fields.name: Curious Oyster
fields.description: These adorable and curious creatures. Wearing shell bonnet and blue dresses, these oysters are overly curious and easily swayed

fields.name: Talking Doorknob
fields.description: Doorknobs are generally nice beings, who tend to be quite kind to visitors. He tends to use humor to lighten serious situations

fields.name: The Mad Hatters Hat
fields.description: Replica of the hat worn by the hatter during one of his famous Unbirthday Parties. Perfect for any collector

fields.name: Shrinking Potion
fields.description: Just one sip of our shrinking potion and you will be small enough to fit through anything

fields.name: Broomdog
fields.description: This hard working dog like creature will keep himself busy cleaning up after anyone who walks on his path

fields.name: Mome Raths
fields.description: These bipedal, flower-like creatures have a pair of googly eyes and fuzzy hair on their heads. When they sleep, only their fuzzy hair is visible. The perfect addition to any garden, just make sure to remind visitor DON'T STEP ON THE MOME RATHS! Please Note: each order will include 10 Mome Raths

fields.name: Hammer and Pencil Birds
fields.description: This hard working pair work together to get the job done. They can often to seen building the signs around Wonderland. Please Note: These birds come in pairs

fields.name: Glasses Bird
fields.description: As you can guess, this bird gets its name because of its resemblance to a pair of glasses. The enjoy having a fun with the Mirror bird by allowing humans to wear them like glasses

fields.name: Flamingo
fields.description: As used by the Queen of Hearts in her game of croquet. Complete the set by picking up Hedgehog too

fields.name: Hedgehog
fields.description: As used by the Queen of Hearts in her game of croquet. Complete the set by picking up Falmingo too

fields.name: Growing Cookies
fields.description: Always wanted to be a bit taller? Then why not try out of Growth cookies. WARNING: Eating too much can lead to uncontrollable growing

fields.name: The Queen Of Hearts Crown
fields.description: Replica of the crown worn by the Queen of Hearts during one of her croquet match against Alice on her first visit to Wonderland. Perfect for any collector

fields.name: Tea with the March Hare
fields.description: Whatever you do, Don't be LATE FOR TEA! This rare opportunity to have afternoon tea with the one and only March Hare is the perfect afternoon for any Wonderland fan

fields.name: The White Rabbits Pocket Watch
fields.description: Never be late again with this replica of the famous White Rabbit Pocket Watch

fields.name: Umbrella Vultures
fields.description: These vultures are in the shape of an umbrella. They like to bathe in ponds and streams but don't get too close as they can be quite an intimidating creature

fields.name: Wonderland Road Signs
fields.description: Built by the Hammer and Pencil Birds, these signs create the ultimate Wonderland feel in any house

fields.name: Shovel Bird
fields.description: As the name suggested, this bird is called so because it's beak is in the shape of a shovel. Keep an eye on them as they can often be caight digging up peoples gardens

fields.name: Drum and Saucer Frogs
fields.description: These musical creatures are shaped like a drum and saucer and make music when they jump. Please Note: these frogs come in pairs
